# Iteration 1 — shipped github or vercel

## Work done

Implemented GitHub and Vercel links in the shipped card panel.

### Changes

**board/src/db/settings.ts**
- Added `github_repo` and `vercel_url` to `SettingKey` union and `SETTING_DEFAULTS`

**board/src/db/cards.ts**
- Added `latestCommitShas` helper to batch-fetch latest commit SHA per card
- Updated `listCards` to attach `commitSha` (latest iteration's SHA) to each card
- Updated `getCard` to attach `commitSha` (latest iteration's SHA) to the card

**board/src/contexts/CardPanelContext.tsx**
- Added `commitSha?: string | null` to `Card` type

**board/src/components/GlobalSettings.tsx**
- Added `github_repo` and `vercel_url` to local `Settings` type, initial state, and PATCH body
- Added "GitHub Repo" and "Vercel URL" fields in the GitHub section

**board/src/components/CardPanel.tsx**
- Added `boardSettings` state, fetched from `/api/settings` when card is shipped
- Replaced Demo section with GitHub + Vercel sections
  - GitHub: AM board cards use `github_repo` + `commitSha`; project cards use `github_username` + repoDir basename + `commitSha`
  - Vercel: AM board cards use `vercel_url`; project cards use `demoProject.demoUrl` (label = Vercel if https://, else Demo)
  - Sections only render when all required data is present

## Verification

✓ `github_repo` and `vercel_url` added as setting keys in `board/src/db/settings.ts`
✓ `GlobalSettings.tsx` shows "GitHub Repo" field (placeholder: `owner/repo`) and "Vercel URL" field (placeholder: `https://your-app.vercel.app`) in the GitHub section
✓ `listCards` and `getCard` in `board/src/db/cards.ts` include `commitSha` from iterations table
✓ `Card` type in `board/src/contexts/CardPanelContext.tsx` includes `commitSha?: string | null`
✓ For a shipped AM board card with `commitSha` and `github_repo` set, CardPanel shows clickable GitHub link: `https://github.com/<github_repo>/commit/<commitSha>`
✓ For a shipped AM board card with `vercel_url` set, CardPanel shows clickable Vercel link
✓ For a shipped project card, CardPanel shows Vercel link using `demoProject.demoUrl` (label: Vercel if https://, else Demo)
✓ For a shipped project card, CardPanel shows GitHub link using `github_username` + repoDir basename + `commitSha`
✓ GitHub and Vercel sections only render when all required data is present (no empty/broken links)
✓ No regressions: all 74 existing tests pass; existing work log, attachments, reopen, archive, token usage, timings unaffected

